# Content Ingestion Pipeline Runbook

This runbook documents the 20TB content processing pipeline â€” how to batch process video, audio, PDFs, and docs from the external drive into Neon Postgres.

## Overview

The pipeline ingests content from external storage across 5 brands, processes each file type appropriately, and stores structured metadata and extracted text in the Neon Postgres database.

**Infrastructure:**
- **Database:** Neon Postgres project `dark-heart-11924323`
- **Schema:** `command_center.content_items`, `content_products`, `processing_queue`
- **Repo:** `rtmendes/content-processor` (processing scripts and workers)
- **Storage:** External drive (20TB across 5 brands)

## Supported File Types

| File Type | Extensions | Processing Method | Avg Time per File |
|-----------|-----------|-------------------|-------------------|
| Video | `.mp4`, `.mov`, `.avi`, `.mkv` | FFmpeg â†’ transcript extraction â†’ metadata | 2-5 min |
| Audio | `.mp3`, `.wav`, `.m4a`, `.ogg` | Whisper transcription â†’ text extraction | 1-3 min |
| PDF | `.pdf` | PyPDF2/pdfplumber â†’ text extraction + OCR fallback | 10-30 sec |
| Documents | `.docx`, `.doc`, `.txt`, `.rtf` | python-docx / direct read â†’ text extraction | 5-15 sec |
| Spreadsheets | `.xlsx`, `.csv` | pandas â†’ structured data extraction | 5-20 sec |
| Images | `.jpg`, `.png`, `.webp` | OCR (Tesseract) â†’ alt-text generation | 15-45 sec |

## Step-by-Step Batch Processing Workflow

### 1. Prepare the Processing Queue

```sql
-- Check current queue status
SELECT status, COUNT(*) 
FROM command_center.processing_queue 
GROUP BY status;

-- Add new batch from external drive scan
INSERT INTO command_center.processing_queue (file_path, file_type, brand, status, created_at)
SELECT file_path, file_type, brand, 'pending', NOW()
FROM command_center.content_items
WHERE processed = false AND file_size > 0;
```

### 2. Start the Batch Processor

```bash
# Clone/pull the processor repo
git clone https://github.com/rtmendes/content-processor.git
cd content-processor

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Run batch processing (default: 10 concurrent workers)
python batch_processor.py --brand "all" --workers 10 --batch-size 500

# Or process a specific brand
python batch_processor.py --brand "insightprofit" --workers 5
```

### 3. Monitor Progress

```sql
-- Real-time progress check
SELECT 
  brand,
  status,
  COUNT(*) as count,
  ROUND(COUNT(*) * 100.0 / SUM(COUNT(*)) OVER (PARTITION BY brand), 1) as pct
FROM command_center.processing_queue
GROUP BY brand, status
ORDER BY brand, status;
```

### 4. Verify Completion

```sql
-- Check for any failed items
SELECT file_path, error_message, retry_count
FROM command_center.processing_queue
WHERE status = 'failed'
ORDER BY updated_at DESC
LIMIT 50;

-- Summary stats
SELECT 
  brand,
  COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE status = 'completed') as completed,
  COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE status = 'failed') as failed,
  COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE status = 'pending') as pending
FROM command_center.processing_queue
GROUP BY brand;
```

## Failure Handling and Recovery

### Retry Failed Items

```sql
-- Reset failed items for retry (max 3 retries)
UPDATE command_center.processing_queue
SET status = 'pending', retry_count = retry_count + 1, error_message = NULL
WHERE status = 'failed' AND retry_count < 3;
```

### Common Failures

| Error | Cause | Fix |
|-------|-------|-----|
| `FileNotFoundError` | External drive disconnected | Reconnect drive, verify mount point |
| `OutOfMemoryError` | Large video file | Reduce `--workers` to 2-3, increase swap |
| `TranscriptionTimeout` | Audio > 2 hours | Split file with `ffmpeg -ss` before processing |
| `OCRError` | Corrupted or DRM-protected PDF | Skip file, log for manual review |
| `ConnectionError` | Neon connection pool exhausted | Reduce workers, check Neon dashboard |

### Nuclear Reset (use sparingly)

```sql
-- Reset ALL failed items
UPDATE command_center.processing_queue
SET status = 'pending', retry_count = 0, error_message = NULL
WHERE status = 'failed';

-- Clear and rebuild queue for a specific brand
DELETE FROM command_center.processing_queue WHERE brand = 'insightprofit';
-- Then re-run step 1
```

## Batch Processing Strategy for 20TB Across 5 Brands

| Phase | Brands | Est. Files | Est. Time | Priority |
|-------|--------|-----------|-----------|----------|
| Phase 1 | InsightProfit | ~50K files | 3-5 days | Highest |
| Phase 2 | Family Gift Studio | ~30K files | 2-3 days | High |
| Phase 3 | Aviation/Pilot Career | ~20K files | 1-2 days | Medium |
| Phase 4 | Polsia AI | ~15K files | 1-2 days | Medium |
| Phase 5 | Personal/Archive | ~100K+ files | 5-7 days | Low |

**Recommended approach:** Process one brand at a time to avoid overwhelming the Neon connection pool. Run overnight batches with `--workers 10` during off-peak hours.

## Cost Summary

| Service | Monthly Cost | Notes |
|---------|-------------|-------|
| Neon Postgres (Pro) | $19/month | 10GB storage, autoscaling compute |
| Whisper API (if using cloud) | $5-10/month | Only for audio/video transcription |
| OCR (Tesseract, local) | $0 | Open source, runs locally |
| **Total** | **~$19-30/month** | After initial processing, drops to ~$5-10/month maintenance |

